HEADWORD: Jerry-builder
<hw>Jer"ry-build`er</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Prob. fr. the
proper name <ets>Jerry</ets>, familiar form of
<ets>Jeremiah</ets>.]</ety> <def>A professional builder who erects cheap
dwellings of poor materials and unsubstantial and slovenly
construction.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

